spans.text: of the noble Fingal , Oscian , Prince of men !
my thoughts ; my thoughts are of the noble Fingal
speak : our ear is open to all : our swords redress the injured
hurt the maid whom the sons of Fingal guard
the maid whom the sons of Fingal guard
like the back of the ridge-wave
they dug for death with their swords
a mountain-oak covered over with glistering frost
